snippet: Defying expectations and, in some places, bullets, Libyans voted in the first election after more than four decades under Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.
abstract: Libyans vote in the country's historic first election after more than four decades of isolation and totalitarianism under Col Muammar el-Qaddafi; voting, though shadowed by several instances of violence, is surprisingly orderly and robust, with turnout exceeding 60 percent.
lead_paragraph: Defying expectations and, in some places, bullets, Libyans voted in the first election after more than four decades under Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.

headline.seo: Libyans Vote in First Election in More Than 40 Years
